From: qinf-build <build@qinf.local>
Subject: [PATCH] qinf: add ggml_deltanet_pre_state op (Phase 3 — CPU)

PR 4.2.B — qinf downstream patch.

Adds GGML_OP_DELTANET_PRE_STATE end-to-end on the CPU backend with
the real fused forward-compute. Replaces the chained 4-op DeltaNet
decode pre-state graph (l2_norm × 2 + repeat_4d × 2) with a single
op that fuses all 4 into one per-row pass, packing Q and K into a
single output tensor.

Output layout: [head_k_dim, 2 * num_v_heads, n_seq_tokens, n_seqs]
  rows [0, num_v_heads):                   l2(Q) tile-repeated
  rows [num_v_heads, 2 * num_v_heads):     l2(K) tile-repeated

Tile-repeat semantics match ggml_repeat_4d (output[i1] = input[i1 % ne01]).

Equivalence verified by tests/unit/test_deltanet_pre_state.cpp:
  decode-shape 128×16×1×1 → packed 128×64×1×1 — bit-stable vs.
  l2_norm × 2 + repeat_4d × 2 within F32 rounding floor.

This patch must be applied AFTER 0001/0002/0003. apply-all.sh
enforces lexical order.

Files touched:
  ggml/include/ggml.h          — op enum + builder declaration
  ggml/src/ggml.c              — name string, symbol string, OP_COUNT bump,
                                 builder impl
  ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ops.h      — forward-compute declaration
  ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ops.cpp    — forward-compute (fused l2_norm × 2 + repeat × 2)
  ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ggml-cpu.c — dispatch case + n_tasks case

Metal backend deliberately not modified — supports_op default returns
false for unknown ops, which routes the op to the CPU backend
automatically. Real Metal kernel lands in patch 0005.

